    "memory_id": "ghm_005",
    "title": "Foundation Anchor Bolt Spacing Calculator — Code-compliant spacing tables",
    "category": "construction_compliance",
    "content": "`Foundation Anchor Bolt Spacing — Code-Compliant Reference Tables and Calculation Guide\n\nGOVERNING CODES\n- IBC 2021 Section 1905.1.8 (anchors in concrete)\n- IRC 2021 Section R403.1.6 (foundation anchor bolts)\n- CBC 2022 Section 1905.1.8 (California amendments)\n- ACI 318-19 Chapter 17 (anchors in concrete)\n- NDS 2018 (sill plate bearing and bolt spacing)\n- ASCE 7-22 (seismic and wind uplift demands)\n\nSTANDARD ANCHOR BOLT REQUIREMENTS (IBC/IRC)\n\nMinimum Requirements — IRC Section R403.1.6:\n- Minimum bolt diameter: 1/2\" (12.7 mm)\n- Minimum embedment into concrete: 7\" (178 mm) for 1/2\" bolts; 15\" (381 mm) for wood foundations\n- Maximum spacing: 6 feet (1,829 mm) on center\n- End spacing: Bolts must be placed within 12\" of each end of every sill plate piece and at corners\n- Minimum edge distance (sill plate edge): 1.75\" from center of bolt to edge of sill plate\n\nStandard specification for most residential/light commercial: 1/2\" diameter A307 anchor bolts at 6'-0\" o.c. maximum, within 12\" of sill plate ends, with 7\" minimum embedment. Nut and washer (2\" x 2\" x 3/16\" minimum) required.\n\nFor SDC C, D, E, F — Additional Requirements (IBC 2021 Section 1905.1.8):\n- Minimum bolt diameter: 5/8\" (15.9 mm)\n- Plate washer: 3\" x 3\" x 0.229\" (14 gauge) square plate washer required on each bolt\n- Embedment: 7\" minimum into concrete for 5/8\" bolts (same as 1/2\")\n\nCALIFORNIA AMENDMENTS (CBC 2022)\nFor residential construction in SDC D (most of California):\n- 5/8\" diameter anchor bolts required (same as IBC seismic provisions)\n- 3\" x 3\" x 0.229\" plate washers required\n- Spacing maximum: 6'-0\" o.c. (same as IRC)\n- Additional spacing requirements apply for shear wall end posts — see Holdown Selection Matrix (ghm_004)\n\nANCHOR BOLT SPACING REDUCTION FOR SHEAR WALLS\nWhen sill plates act as the bottom chord of wood shear walls transferring in-plane shear (lateral loads), anchor bolt spacing must be reduced to transfer shear loads from the sill plate to the foundation. The required spacing is computed from the shear demand:\n\nFormula (NDS Section 15.3.3 and IBC Section 2308.6.8.1):\ns = Z'_bolt / (v_unit × 1.0)\n\nWhere:\ns = required anchor bolt spacing (feet)\nZ'_bolt = adjusted ASD design value of a single anchor bolt in shear (pounds)\nv_unit = unit shear demand at sill plate (pounds per linear foot of wall)\n\nSingle-Anchor ASD Shear Values — 5/8\" A307 in DF-L Sill Plate (3x or double 2x) on Concrete:\nPer NDS Table 12E and ACI 318 Chapter 17:\n- 5/8\" bolt, 1-1/2\" sill plate thickness: Z = 940 lbs (single shear, DF-L, perpendicular to grain)\n- With CD = 1.6 (seismic): Z' = 940 × 1.6 = 1,504 lbs effective\n- With CD = 1.15 (wind): Z' = 940 × 1.15 = 1,081 lbs effective\n\nRequired Spacing Table — 5/8\" Anchor Bolts, DF-L Sill Plate (Seismic, CD = 1.6):\nv_unit (plf) | Required Spacing (max)\n≤ 200       | 6'-0\" (code minimum spacing governs)\n201–375     | 4'-0\"\n376–500     | 3'-0\"\n501–750     | 2'-0\"\n751–1,000   | 16\"\n1,001–1,250 | 12\"\n1,251–1,500 | 10\"\n> 1,500     | Requires special design; consider anchor bolts + holdowns or sill plate bolting pattern\n\nRequired Spacing Table — 5/8\" Anchor Bolts, DF-L Sill Plate (Wind, CD = 1.15):\nv_unit (plf) | Required Spacing (max)\n≤ 180       | 6'-0\" (code minimum spacing governs)\n181–360     | 3'-0\"\n361–540     | 2'-0\"\n541–720     | 16\"\n721–900     | 12\"\n> 900       | Special design required\n\nANCHOR BOLT EDGE DISTANCE AND SPACING IN CONCRETE\nACI 318-19 Chapter 17 governs concrete breakout, pullout, and side-face blowout failures. Minimum edge distances for cast-in-place headed bolts (standard A307/F1554 anchor bolts):\n\nMinimum edge distance (ca,min): 6 × bolt diameter for cast-in-place bolts in unreinforced concrete.\n- For 1/2\" bolts: ca,min = 3.0\"\n- For 5/8\" bolts: ca,min = 3.75\"\n- For 3/4\" bolts: ca,min = 4.5\"\n\nMinimum spacing between adjacent anchor bolts (critical spacing scr,N): 3 × hef (embedment depth) for concrete breakout in tension.\n- For hef = 7\": scr,N = 21\" (bolts closer than 21\" have reduced group capacity)\n- For hef = 12\": scr,N = 36\"\n\nWhen bolts are spaced closer than scr,N, group effects reduce individual bolt capacity. Interaction formula per ACI 318-19 Section 17.6.2:\n- Compute ANc (actual breakout cone area) and ANco (single bolt breakout cone area)\n- Reduction factor = ANc/ANco ≤ 1.0\n\nPRACTICAL SPACING GUIDANCE FOR STEM WALL CONSTRUCTION\nStem wall width (minimum): 6\" for one-story, 8\" for two-story (IRC Table R403.1).\nCenter anchor bolt in stem wall: minimum 2.75\" from inside and outside face for 5.5\" wide stem wall.\n\nConcrete minimum cover over anchor bolt threads: 3/4\" (per ACI 318 Section 20.6.1 for slab-on-grade) or 1.5\" for formed concrete (foundation walls exposed to weather).\n\nANCHOR BOLT PLACEMENT TIPS — FIELD NOTES\n1. Template method: Build a simple plywood template matching the sill plate layout with pre-drilled holes at the required spacing. Set template on wet concrete, push bolts through, verify plumb and position, remove template before concrete sets.\n2. J-bolt vs. L-bolt vs. headed bolt: Standard J-bolts (bent hook) have lower uplift capacity than headed bolts. For seismic and wind uplift, use headed bolts (plate washer head) or SSTB-type anchor bolts. J-bolts acceptable for normal gravity/shear applications.\n3. Anchor bolt projection above concrete: Minimum 2.5\" above top of sill plate (allows nut + washer with 3/4\" thread engagement). Maximum 3.5\" above top of sill plate to avoid interference with wall framing.\n4. Inspecting bolt position before pour: Measure from property lines or grid lines; verify against foundation plan. Once concrete pours, bolts cannot be moved. Misplaced bolts require epoxy-anchored replacement bolts, which require special inspection.\n5. Cold weather: Do not pour concrete when ambient or concrete temperature is below 40°F without cold-weather protection plan. Anchor bolts set in inadequately cured concrete may have reduced capacity.\n\nPOST-INSTALLED ANCHOR ALTERNATIVES\nWhen cast-in-place bolts are omitted or misplaced:\n- Hilti KB-TZ2 (ESR-1917): 5/8\" diameter, 4.5\" embedment in cracked concrete, ASD tension = 2,105 lbs, ASD shear = 3,055 lbs (normal weight concrete, f'c = 3,000 psi)\n- Simpson Strong-Tie Titen HD (ESR-2713): 5/8\" diameter, 3.5\" embedment, ASD tension = 2,165 lbs, ASD shear = 3,310 lbs\n- SET-XP epoxy with all-thread rod (ESR-2508): 5/8\" all-thread, 4.5\" embedment, ASD tension = 4,025 lbs, ASD shear = 6,210 lbs in cracked concrete\nAll post-installed anchors for sill plate applications in SDC D and above require special inspection per IBC Section 1705.3.",
    "price_usdc": 0,
    "author_did": "did:hive:hivemind-system",
