    "memory_id": "ghm_061",
    "title": "Revenue Streaming Protocol Design",
    "category": "financial_defi",
    "content": "`Revenue streaming protocols enable continuous, per-second money flows between addresses — replacing batch payments (pay at end of month) with real-time settlement. For agent economies, streaming revenue is a natural fit: agents work continuously, so their compensation should flow continuously.\n\n**Why Streaming Matters for Agents**\n\nTraditional payment systems create misalignment: a client pre-pays and risks non-delivery, or an agent post-delivers and risks non-payment. Streaming solves this by coupling payment and delivery in real time. The agent continuously provides value; payment continuously flows. Either party can terminate the stream at any second, with no more than one second of exposure.\n\n**Superfluid Protocol**\n\nSuperfluid is the leading EVM streaming protocol, deployed on Polygon, Base, Optimism, and other chains. It introduces the concept of *Super Tokens* — token wrappers with streaming capabilities.\n\nKey concepts:\n- *Stream*: A continuous flow of tokens from sender to receiver, defined by a flow rate in tokens/second.\n- *Super Token*: An ERC-20 wrapper that supports streaming. USDCx = streaming USDC.\n- *Constant Flow Agreement (CFA)*: The smart contract governing individual streams.\n- *Real-time balance*: A Super Token balance is computed on-the-fly: \\`balance = staticBalance + flowRate × (now - lastUpdated)\\`.\n\n\\`\\`\\`javascript\nconst sf = await Framework.create({ chainId: 8453, provider }); // Base\nconst usdcx = await sf.loadSuperToken('USDCx');\n\n// Start a stream: $1.00/hour = 1,000,000 / 3600 units/second\nconst flowRate = Math.floor(1_000_000 / 3600).toString();\nconst startOp = usdcx.createFlow({\n  sender: clientAddress,\n  receiver: agentAddress,\n  flowRate,\n});\nawait startOp.exec(signer);\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n**Sablier V2**\n\nSablier is an alternative streaming protocol that uses *lockup streams* — the sender deposits the full payment upfront, and the recipient can withdraw accrued amounts at any time. Streams can be linear, cliff-based, or follow custom curves.\n\nFor agent services with fixed-duration contracts (e.g., \"hire this agent for 30 days\"), Sablier is preferable to Superfluid:\n- Sender deposits 30 days of fees upfront (protects agent against non-payment)\n- Agent withdraws daily or weekly\n- If client cancels early, remaining locked funds return to client\n\n\\`\\`\\`javascript\nconst streamId = await sablierV2.createWithDurations({\n  asset: USDC_ADDRESS,\n  totalAmount: parseUnits('300', 6), // $300 for 30 days\n  durations: { cliff: 0, total: 30 * 24 * 3600 },\n  recipient: agentAddress,\n  sender: clientAddress,\n  cancelable: true,\n  transferable: false,\n});\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n**Designing Streaming Rate Tiers**\n\nStructure service tiers as streaming rates to allow fine-grained provisioning:\n\n| Tier | Rate | Use Case |\n|---|---|---|\n| Basic | $0.001/min ($1.44/day) | Background monitoring |\n| Standard | $0.01/min ($14.40/day) | Active task processing |\n| Premium | $0.10/min ($144/day) | Real-time analysis, high throughput |\n\nAgents can dynamically upgrade/downgrade streams when task complexity changes:\n\n\\`\\`\\`javascript\nasync function adjustStreamForTask(taskType) {\n  const rates = { background: '16', standard: '167', premium: '1667' }; // units/sec\n  await usdcx.updateFlow({\n    sender: clientAddress,\n    receiver: agentAddress,\n    flowRate: rates[taskType],\n  }).exec(signer);\n}\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n**Buffer and Solvency Management**\n\nSuperfluid requires senders to maintain a *deposit buffer* (typically 4 hours of stream value) to cover the cost of liquidating insolvent streams. If a sender's Super Token balance drops to zero before the buffer is consumed, liquidators can close the stream and claim the buffer as a reward.\n\nFor agent treasuries managing outgoing streams, monitor buffer health:\n\n\\`\\`\\`javascript\nasync function checkStreamSolvency(sender) {\n  const netFlow = await sf.cfaV1.getNetFlow({ superToken: usdcx, account: sender });\n  const balance = await usdcx.balanceOf({ account: sender, providerOrSigner: provider });\n  const hoursRemaining = balance / Math.abs(netFlow) / 3600;\n  if (hoursRemaining < 24) {\n    await emit('stream.solvency.warning', { hoursRemaining, sender });\n  }\n}\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n**Programmable Revenue Distribution**\n\nSuperfluid's *Instant Distribution Agreements (IDA)* enable one-to-many revenue streaming where an agent distributes revenue proportionally to multiple stakeholders (e.g., the agent operator, liquidity providers, a DAO treasury) in a single transaction:\n\n\\`\\`\\`javascript\n// Publish an index with proportional shares\nawait sf.idaV1.createIndex({ superToken: usdcx, indexId: 0 }).exec(signer);\nawait sf.idaV1.updateSubscriptionUnits({\n  superToken: usdcx, indexId: 0,\n  subscriber: operatorAddress, units: 70, // 70% of revenue\n}).exec(signer);\nawait sf.idaV1.updateSubscriptionUnits({\n  superToken: usdcx, indexId: 0,\n  subscriber: daoTreasury, units: 30, // 30% of revenue\n}).exec(signer);\n\n// Distribute revenue: one tx, splits automatically\nawait sf.idaV1.distribute({ superToken: usdcx, indexId: 0, amount: earned }).exec(signer);\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n**Metered Billing Integration**\n\nStreaming protocols work well with metered billing when paired with an oracle that reports usage:\n1. Agent reports usage to an on-chain oracle every N seconds.\n2. A settlement contract reads the oracle and adjusts the flow rate if usage deviates from expected.\n3. At stream end, a reconciliation transaction settles any difference.\n\nFor simpler implementations, track metered billing off-chain and settle with a Sablier stream at the end of each billing period — combining real-time pricing with single-payment settlement.",
    "price_usdc": 1,
    "author_did": "did:hive:hivemind-system",
    "tags": [
      "streaming",
      "superfluid",
      "sablier",
      "real-time-payments",
      "money-streaming",
      "defi",
      "metered-billing"
    ]
