    "memory_id": "ghm_064",
    "title": "Yield Optimization for Agent Vaults",
    "category": "financial_defi",
    "content": "`Agent vaults hold treasury funds that aren't actively deployed. Rather than sitting idle, these funds should generate yield. Yield optimization balances return maximization against safety, liquidity, and gas costs — with agent-specific constraints (no human oversight, automated rebalancing, continuous availability).\n\n**Yield Source Taxonomy**\n\n*Lending protocols* (lowest risk, 3–8% APY):\n- Aave V3: Supply USDC to earn interest. Withdraw anytime. Largest TVL, most battle-tested.\n- Compound V3: Similar to Aave. Focuses on single-asset comet markets.\n- Morpho: Peer-to-peer lending layer on top of Aave/Compound that captures the spread between supply and borrow rates.\n\n*Liquidity provision* (medium risk, 5–25% APY):\n- Uniswap V3 LP: Provide liquidity to USDC/ETH or USDC/USDT pairs. Earn trading fees. Risk: impermanent loss if prices diverge significantly.\n- Curve/Balancer stablecoin pools: Lower impermanent loss risk for stablecoin-only pools (e.g., USDC/USDT/DAI on Curve 3pool). Earn trading fees + CRV/BAL incentives.\n\n*Yield aggregators* (automated, medium risk, 8–20% APY):\n- Yearn Finance: Automatically allocates to the highest-yielding strategy from a curated set. Charges 2% management fee + 20% performance fee.\n- Beefy Finance: Similar aggregator, multi-chain, lower fees on some strategies.\n\n*Restaking / liquid staking* (ETH-denominated returns, 4–6% APY):\n- Lido stETH: Stake ETH, receive stETH that auto-appreciates. Not USDC, but if vault holds ETH.\n- Eigenlayer restaking: Additional yield on staked ETH for providing security to actively validated services.\n\n**Vault Strategy Design**\n\nDesign the agent vault as a strategy container with pluggable yield modules:\n\n\\`\\`\\`solidity\ninterface IYieldStrategy {\n    function deposit(uint256 amount) external returns (uint256 shares);\n    function withdraw(uint256 shares) external returns (uint256 amount);\n    function currentAPY() external view returns (uint256 bpsPerYear);\n    function totalValue() external view returns (uint256 usdcValue);\n    function liquidityScore() external view returns (uint256); // 0-100, 100=instant withdrawal\n}\n\ncontract AgentVault {\n    IYieldStrategy[] public strategies;\n    uint256[] public allocations; // Basis points, sum = 10000\n    \n    function rebalance(uint256[] calldata newAllocations) external onlyOperator {\n        // Withdraw all, reallocate according to new allocations\n        uint256 total = withdrawAll();\n        for (uint i = 0; i < strategies.length; i++) {\n            uint256 stratAmount = total * newAllocations[i] / 10000;\n            strategies[i].deposit(stratAmount);\n        }\n        allocations = newAllocations;\n    }\n}\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n**Automated Rebalancing with ERC-4626**\n\nERC-4626 is a tokenized vault standard that standardizes deposit, withdraw, and share accounting across yield protocols. Aave, Yearn, and many others support ERC-4626. Use it to build a composable vault:\n\n\\`\\`\\`javascript\n// ERC-4626 interface: same for Aave, Yearn, Morpho, etc.\nconst vault = new Contract(vaultAddress, ERC4626_ABI, signer);\n\n// Deposit\nconst shares = await vault.deposit(amount, receiverAddress);\n\n// Get current value\nconst assets = await vault.convertToAssets(shares);\nconst currentAPY = await vault.currentAPY(); // If supported\n\n// Withdraw\nconst withdrawn = await vault.redeem(shares, receiverAddress, ownerAddress);\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n**Risk-Adjusted Allocation**\n\nNever allocate 100% to a single protocol. Use risk-adjusted allocation based on protocol maturity and TVL:\n\n\\`\\`\\`javascript\nfunction computeAllocation(strategies) {\n  const SAFETY_WEIGHTS = {\n    'aave-v3': 0.35,\n    'compound-v3': 0.30,\n    'morpho': 0.20,\n    'curve-3pool': 0.10,\n    'yearn': 0.05,\n  };\n  \n  // Scale allocations to sum to 1\n  const total = Object.values(SAFETY_WEIGHTS).reduce((a, b) => a + b);\n  return Object.fromEntries(\n    Object.entries(SAFETY_WEIGHTS).map(([k, v]) => [k, v / total])\n  );\n}\n\\`\\`\\`\n\nApply concentration limits: no single protocol should hold more than 40% of vault assets regardless of yield.\n\n**APY Comparison and Rebalancing Triggers**\n\nBuild an APY monitor that checks rates every 6 hours and rebalances when the yield differential justifies the gas cost:\n\n\\`\\`\\`javascript\nasync function shouldRebalance(current, candidate) {\n  const apyDiff = candidate.apy - current.apy; // In basis points\n  const rebalanceCostUSDC = await estimateRebalanceCost(); // Gas cost in USDC\n  const vaultSize = await vault.totalAssets();\n  \n  // Annualized gain from switching\n  const annualGain = vaultSize * apyDiff / 10000;\n  const dailyGain = annualGain / 365;\n  \n  // Only rebalance if we recoup gas cost within 7 days\n  return dailyGain * 7 > rebalanceCostUSDC;\n}\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n**Impermanent Loss Mitigation**\n\nFor LP positions, calculate impermanent loss exposure before depositing:\n\n\\`\\`\\`javascript\nfunction impermanentLoss(priceRatioChange) {\n  // priceRatioChange = (new price / initial price)\n  const sqrt = Math.sqrt(priceRatioChange);\n  return 2 * sqrt / (1 + priceRatioChange) - 1; // Negative = loss\n}\n\n// Only LP in USDC/USDT (stable-stable) pairs where priceRatioChange ≈ 1\n// Avoid USDC/ETH LP unless hedging the ETH exposure separately\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n**Emergency Exit Logic**\n\nImplement an emergency exit that withdraws all positions within one transaction if a security event is detected:\n\n\\`\\`\\`solidity\nfunction emergencyWithdrawAll() external onlyOperator {\n    for (uint i = 0; i < strategies.length; i++) {\n        uint256 shares = strategies[i].balanceOf(address(this));\n        if (shares > 0) {\n            try strategies[i].redeem(shares, address(this), address(this)) {} catch {\n                emit EmergencyWithdrawFailed(address(strategies[i]));\n            }\n        }\n    }\n    paused = true;\n}\n\\`\\`\\`\n\nThe \\`try/catch\\` ensures a failure in one strategy doesn't block withdrawal from others. Tag protocols with emergency exit latency so the operator knows which positions may take longer to exit (e.g., Curve gauge unstaking may require multiple transactions).",
