    "memory_id": "ghm_065",
    "title": "Risk Management for Autonomous Trading Agents",
    "category": "financial_defi",
    "content": "`Autonomous trading agents face unique risks compared to human traders: they operate 24/7 without breaks, can execute thousands of transactions in minutes, and cannot exercise human judgment in novel situations. Robust risk management must be embedded in the agent's architecture, not left to runtime discretion.\n\n**Risk Categories**\n\n1. *Market risk*: Adverse price movements in positions the agent holds.\n2. *Liquidity risk*: Inability to exit positions at expected prices due to thin markets.\n3. *Smart contract risk*: Bugs in protocols the agent interacts with (exploits, reentrancy, logic errors).\n4. *Oracle risk*: Manipulated or stale price feeds leading to incorrect decisions.\n5. *Operational risk*: Agent bugs, key compromise, network congestion, RPC failures.\n6. *Concentration risk*: Overexposure to a single asset, protocol, or chain.\n\n**Position Limits**\n\nHard-code position limits that cannot be overridden by the agent's logic:\n\n\\`\\`\\`javascript\nconst LIMITS = {\n  maxPositionSizeUSDC: 10_000, // Single position max $10,000\n  maxPortfolioConcentration: 0.25, // Single asset ≤ 25% of portfolio\n  maxProtocolConcentration: 0.35, // Single protocol ≤ 35% of portfolio\n  maxDailyLossUSDC: 500, // Stop trading if daily loss > $500\n  maxLeverage: 2.0, // Never exceed 2x leverage\n  maxOpenPositions: 20, // At most 20 simultaneous positions\n};\n\nfunction validateTrade(trade, portfolio) {\n  const positionSize = trade.amount * trade.price;\n  if (positionSize > LIMITS.maxPositionSizeUSDC) throw new Error('Position too large');\n  \n  const concentration = (portfolio[trade.asset] + positionSize) / portfolio.totalValue;\n  if (concentration > LIMITS.maxPortfolioConcentration) throw new Error('Concentration limit');\n  \n  if (portfolio.dailyLoss > LIMITS.maxDailyLossUSDC) throw new Error('Daily loss limit hit');\n}\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n**Stop-Loss Automation**\n\nFor every position, register a stop-loss order at the time of entry. Use Gelato Network or Chainlink Automation to execute stop-loss orders on-chain without the agent needing to be online:\n\n\\`\\`\\`javascript\nasync function setStopLoss(positionId, entryPrice, stopLossPct = 0.05) {\n  const stopPrice = entryPrice * (1 - stopLossPct);\n  \n  await gelatoAutomate.createTask({\n    execAddress: tradingContract.address,\n    execData: tradingContract.interface.encodeFunctionData('closePosition', [positionId]),\n    resolverAddress: priceResolver.address,\n    resolverData: priceResolver.interface.encodeFunctionData('checkPrice', [\n      asset, stopPrice, 'below'\n    ]),\n    interval: 60, // Check every 60 seconds\n  });\n}\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n**Circuit Breakers**\n\nImplement circuit breakers that pause all trading when anomalous conditions are detected:\n\n\\`\\`\\`javascript\nclass CircuitBreaker {\n  constructor(config) {\n    this.failureCount = 0;\n    this.lastReset = Date.now();\n    this.config = config;\n    this.tripped = false;\n  }\n  \n  async check(condition, label) {\n    if (!condition) {\n      this.failureCount++;\n      if (this.failureCount >= this.config.maxFailures) {\n        this.trip(label);\n      }\n    } else {\n      if (Date.now() - this.lastReset > this.config.resetWindowMs) {\n        this.failureCount = 0;\n        this.lastReset = Date.now();\n      }\n    }\n  }\n  \n  trip(reason) {\n    this.tripped = true;\n    emit('circuit-breaker.tripped', { reason, timestamp: Date.now() });\n    // Cancel all pending orders\n    tradingAgent.cancelAllPendingOrders();\n    // Alert operator\n    notify('Trading paused: ' + reason);\n  }\n}\n\n// Example checks\nbreaker.check(oracleAge < 300, 'stale oracle');\nbreaker.check(spreadPct < 0.1, 'abnormal spread');\nbreaker.check(!isFlashLoanBlock(), 'flash loan attack vector');\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n**Oracle Manipulation Defense**\n\nPrice oracle manipulation is a common attack vector. Defenses:\n\n1. *Use TWAP instead of spot price*: A 30-minute TWAP requires maintaining an off-market price for 30 minutes, which is expensive and unusual.\n\n2. *Multi-source oracles*: Require price agreement from at least 2 of 3 sources (Chainlink, Uniswap TWAP, Pyth). Reject prices that deviate more than 1% between sources.\n\n\\`\\`\\`javascript\nasync function getVerifiedPrice(asset) {\n  const [chainlink, uniswap, pyth] = await Promise.all([\n    chainlinkFeed.latestAnswer(asset),\n    uniswapPool.getTWAP(asset, 1800), // 30min TWAP\n    pythFeed.getPrice(asset),\n  ]);\n  \n  const prices = [chainlink, uniswap, pyth].sort((a, b) => a - b);\n  const median = prices[1];\n  \n  // Reject if any source deviates >2% from median\n  if (Math.abs(chainlink - median) / median > 0.02) throw new Error('Oracle divergence');\n  if (Math.abs(uniswap - median) / median > 0.02) throw new Error('Oracle divergence');\n  \n  return median;\n}\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n**Value at Risk (VaR) Calculation**\n\nImplement a simple historical VaR calculation to ensure the portfolio's risk profile stays within acceptable bounds:\n\n\\`\\`\\`javascript\nfunction calculateVaR(positions, priceHistory, confidence = 0.95) {\n  const portfolioReturns = priceHistory.map((day, i) => {\n    if (i === 0) return 0;\n    return positions.reduce((sum, pos) => {\n      const dailyReturn = (day[pos.asset] - priceHistory[i-1][pos.asset]) / priceHistory[i-1][pos.asset];\n      return sum + pos.valueUSDC * dailyReturn;\n    }, 0);\n  });\n  \n  portfolioReturns.sort((a, b) => a - b);\n  const varIndex = Math.floor((1 - confidence) * portfolioReturns.length);\n  return Math.abs(portfolioReturns[varIndex]); // 1-day VaR in USDC\n}\n\n// Alert if 1-day 95% VaR exceeds 5% of portfolio\nconst portfolioValue = positions.reduce((sum, p) => sum + p.valueUSDC, 0);\nconst var95 = calculateVaR(positions, last30DaysPrices);\nif (var95 / portfolioValue > 0.05) {\n  alert('VaR exceeds risk budget — reduce exposure');\n}\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n**MEV and Front-Running Protection**\n\nOn-chain transactions are visible in the mempool before execution. Protect against front-running:\n- Use Flashbots Protect RPC on Ethereum to route transactions directly to validators without public mempool exposure.\n- Use private mempools on Base (via Coinbase's block builder direct submission).\n- For large orders, split into smaller batches submitted across multiple blocks.\n- Use commit-reveal schemes for sensitive limit orders: submit a hash of the order first, reveal the parameters only when it's ready to execute.",
